en_971483_1	The two countries will sign the missile deal, estimated at more than $5 billion, during Putin’s visit beginning a Kremlin aide.
en_971483_2	The United States has warned India against a planned purchase of S-400 surface-to-air missiles from Russia during Putin’s visit, saying such an acquisition would attract sanctions under U.S. law.
en_971483_3	India’s military wants the missile batteries, both as a deterrent against China and to gain an edge over traditional rival, Pakistan, as they are able to track and shoot down combat aircraft, even stealth planes, at unprecedented ranges.
